-- Advanced Medical bids for Bausch & Lomb: sources
-- 
-- Thu Jul 5, 2007 5:55pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/05/us-advancedmedical-offer-idUSN0538214820070705

 

 PHILADELPHIA  (Reuters) - Advanced Medical Optics Inc. EYE.N has offered to buy rival eye-care company Bausch & Lomb Inc. BOL.N for $4.23 billion, topping a rival offer of $3.67 billion from private equity firm Warburg Pincus WP.UL, sources familiar with the situation said on Thursday. 

 Advanced Medical's offer is valued at $75 a share, of which $45 is in cash and $30 in stock, sources said. That compares with a $65 per share offer made by Warburg Pincus in May.